catalog.title: Clinical Process Comm Dis
catalog.description: The course focuses on development of treatment plans, establishment of objectives, tracking of treament progress, written reports, professional ethical behavior and clinical problem solving.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci

notes.note:
Previous CDS 502 AUD is now CDS503 AUD
Same course content

catalog.title: Aud Research Methods
catalog.description: This course will focus on the application of research methodologies and their application in daily clinical problems. Topics covered include hypothesis driven research, considering different variables and effectors, the basic science and clinical application of different research designs, statistical methods, research ethics with particular attention to the clinical practice, and evidence-based medicine.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci

catalog.title: Evaluating Clinical Change
catalog.description: This course will focus on the application of research methodologies to solve clinically relevant problems in the field of communicative disorders. Topics covered include the clinical application of single case designs, group-level designs, statistical methods needed for clinical research and practice, the ethics of clinical practice and research, and evidence-based practice.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci

notes.note: Knowledge of Excel spreadsheets is recommended for this course.

catalog.title: Phonological Dis: Diag & Mgmt
catalog.description: Introduction to sound acquisition in typically developing children and atypically developing children who exhibit speech or phonological disorders. Examine the major etiologies of speech disorders and coexisting conditions correlated with phonological disorders. Case studies will introduce various aspects of a comprehensive phonological evaluation and data analyses, and current approaches to phonological remediation.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci

catalog.title: Practicum: Audiology 2
catalog.description: Students pursuing their Doctorate of Audiology provide diagnostic and therapeutic services under the supervision of externship supervisors in accordance with ASHA guidelines.  Students are assigned externship placements in the beginning of each semester.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci

catalog.title: Practicum: Sp & Lang 2
catalog.description: Students pursuing their Masters degree in Speech-Language Pathology provide diagnostic and therapeutic services under the supervision of externship supervisors in accordance with ASHA guidelines.  Students are assigned externship placements in the beginning of each semester.  Upon entrance into their first year of graduate study students (excluding promising students, make-up students, or students working on mastering the English language) will be scheduled a clinic caseload.  Promising students, make-up students, or students perfecting their verbal or written standard American English skills will be scheduled to enter the clinic upon the discretion of academic and clinical advisors. Clinic assignments will be made at the beginning of each semester with additional assignments made as necessary.  Clinic assignments will be made to accommodate for each student's academic courses, but will not be made to accommodate for outside commitments.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci

catalog.title: Lang Dis in School-Age Pop
catalog.description: Disorders of spoken and written language in the school-age population, etiologies, assessment, and intervention approaches will be reviewed.
catalog.subject: Communicative Disorders & Sci
catalog.long_title: Language Disorders in the School-Age Population
